  <div class="sec-mark" id="faq">// Frequently asked questions</div>

  <div class="faq-list" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/FAQPage">

    <details class="faq" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
      <summary><span itemprop="name">What is the best free AI tool for Shopify store owners in 2026?</span><span class="faq-ico" aria-hidden="true"></span></summary>
      <div class="faq-ans" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
        <p itemprop="text">The best free AI tools for Shopify in 2026 are <strong>Systeme.io</strong> (replaces Klaviyo at $0 for up to 2,000 contacts with unlimited sends), <strong>Make.com</strong> (automates Shopify workflows free for 1,000 ops/month), <strong>Beehiiv</strong> (brand newsletter free for up to 2,500 subscribers), <strong>Tidio</strong> (AI customer support with a genuinely functional free tier), and <strong>Shopify Magic</strong> (built into every Shopify plan for product descriptions). These five tools cover the most expensive Shopify AI use cases before you spend anything.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="faq" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
      <summary><span itemprop="name">Is Systeme.io a good free alternative to Klaviyo for Shopify?</span><span class="faq-ico" aria-hidden="true"></span></summary>
      <div class="faq-ans" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
        <p itemprop="text">Yes. Systeme.io is the most effective free Klaviyo alternative for Shopify stores in 2026. The free plan includes 2,000 contacts with unlimited email sends, full abandoned cart and post-purchase automation, sales funnels, and CRM — everything most stores use Klaviyo for. Klaviyo's free plan is limited to 250 contacts and 500 emails per month. Systeme.io's free plan handles 8× more contacts with no email send limit. Stores paying $150–$400/month for Klaviyo can migrate to Systeme.io's free plan in approximately 30 minutes. See the <a href="https://www.stackarchitect.xyz/replace-klaviyo-free">free step-by-step migration guide</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="faq" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
      <summary><span itemprop="name">What does Make.com do for Shopify stores?</span><span class="faq-ico" aria-hidden="true"></span></summary>
      <div class="faq-ans" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
        <p itemprop="text">Make.com connects Shopify to 1,500+ apps through visual automation workflows. For Shopify stores, the most valuable use cases are: (1) sending server-side conversion events to Meta and Google via CAPI Shield, (2) syncing orders to Google Sheets in real time for inventory and P&L tracking, (3) connecting Shopify webhooks to Systeme.io for email automation, and (4) sending low-stock alerts to Slack or Gmail. Make.com's free plan includes 1,000 operations per month — enough for most small stores to run all of these automations simultaneously at $0.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="faq" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
      <summary><span itemprop="name">How much does Make.com cost compared to Zapier for Shopify?</span><span class="faq-ico" aria-hidden="true"></span></summary>
      <div class="faq-ans" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
        <p itemprop="text">Make.com's free plan includes 1,000 operations per month. Zapier's free plan includes only 100 tasks per month — 10× fewer than Make.com. For paid plans, Make.com's Core plan costs $9/month for 10,000 operations. Zapier's equivalent Starter plan costs $19.99/month for 750 tasks. For most Shopify automation use cases, Make.com delivers significantly more capacity at a lower price. The main trade-off is that Make.com has a steeper learning curve than Zapier's simpler interface.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="faq" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
      <summary><span itemprop="name">Is Tidio worth it for Shopify customer support?</span><span class="faq-ico" aria-hidden="true"></span></summary>
      <div class="faq-ans" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
        <p itemprop="text">For Shopify stores under £50,000 per month GMV, Tidio's free tier handles the majority of customer support needs. Lyro AI automatically resolves order status queries, shipping questions, and product FAQs — the categories that account for 60–70% of Shopify support volume. The free tier is capped at 50 Lyro AI conversations per month. For higher volume, Tidio's paid plans start at $29/month — significantly less than Gorgias at £60–£300/month. The native Shopify integration pulls live order data so Lyro can answer "where is my order?" without a human agent.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="faq" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
      <summary><span itemprop="name">What AI tools replace the most expensive Shopify apps in 2026?</span><span class="faq-ico" aria-hidden="true"></span></summary>
      <div class="faq-ans" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
        <p itemprop="text">The highest-ROI AI tool replacements for Shopify in 2026 are: Systeme.io replaces Klaviyo at $0 (saves $150–$400/month), Make.com replaces Zapier and automation connectors (saves $50–$200/month), Tidio replaces Gorgias for customer support (saves £60–£300/month), Photoroom replaces product photography shoots, and Beehiiv replaces paid newsletter platforms. Combined with the $0 Shopify automation stack (CAPI Shield, Stocky Swap, P&L Auto), stores can replace six paid apps worth $700+/month at zero cost.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="faq" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
      <summary><span itemprop="name">Should I use Beehiiv or Systeme.io for Shopify email?</span><span class="faq-ico" aria-hidden="true"></span></summary>
      <div class="faq-ans" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
        <p itemprop="text">Use both — they serve different purposes. <strong>Systeme.io</strong> is built for e-commerce transactional email: abandoned cart, welcome sequences, post-purchase flows, and Shopify webhook-triggered automations. <strong>Beehiiv</strong> is built for brand newsletters: curated content, subscriber growth, and newsletter monetisation. The recommended setup: Systeme.io for all Shopify-triggered flows and Beehiiv for a weekly or monthly brand newsletter. Together they replace a $300+/month Klaviyo and newsletter platform stack at $0 until you exceed 2,000–2,500 subscribers.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

  </div>

